body:
Actually it would be bad to just rename the method, as that would break indexing for current implementers of the interface.

How about adding an additional interface, and trying both to determine the type.  E.g.:

``` go
// (Deprecated:  use BleveClassifier).  A Classifier is an interface describing any object
// which knows how to identify its own type.
type Classifier interface {
    Type() string
}

// A BleveClassifier is an interface describing any object
// which knows how to identify its own document type.
type BleveClassifier interface {
    BleveType() string
}
```

Then within the IndexMapping.determineType method, add a check for the new type.
